1601352000.title: Bargain Hunt
1601352000.descr: Two teams of amateur antique collectors meet at an antiques fair to compete to make the largest profit from a three hundred pound budget. Once the contestants have done the shopping for their own items, the experts then take any leftover money and go shopping for more antiques which is 'bonus buys'. The teams then have to decide whether or not to take these items to auction.

1601354700.title: Last of the Summer Wine
1601354700.descr: Clegg is writing his memoirs, but is having trouble remembering people's names; Clegg, Truly and Billy meet a man who wants to sail to Ilkley in an inflatable swan, unfortunately it has developed a puncture which Entwistle repairs; Clegg climbs a tree so he can see the church clock, unfortunately he gets stuck; Tom and Entwistle try to cheer Smiler up after he has been dumped by Hermione.

1601356500.title: Hold the Sunset
1601356500.descr: With John Cleese, James Cosmo, Suzanne Packer, Anne Reid, Alexandra Roach, Joanna Scanlan. Sitcom. Bob gives Roger the idea of applying to be a paid carer for Edith. However, Edith is perfectly well, so who can Roger persuade to stand in for her?

1601358300.title: Call the Midwife
1601358300.descr: Period drama series set in East London in the 1950s, following the life and work of a young midwife Jenny Lee and her colleagues at the Nonnatus House nursing convent. They serve the poor society of Poplar, London. Their main duty is to help bring safe birth to women and help them look after their newborns.

1601361600.title: Impossible
1601361600.descr: Entertaining and educational British quiz show, hosted by Rick Edwards, where 24 regular contestants compete throughout the series to answer tricky questions. But some of the optional answers are designed to be ''impossible'', or at the very least inconsistent with the information given. The participants must avoid selecting these booby trap answer and the best one wins the £10,000 jackpot.

1601402400.title: Last of the Summer Wine
1601402400.descr: Classic British sitcom following the misadventures of a trio of elderly men from a Yorkshire village who never tire of playing tricks on their fellow townspeople. The series is Britain's longest-running comedy programme and has received many praises for its family-friendly humour and portrayal of older people.

1601404200.title: Hold the Sunset
1601404200.descr: With Rosie Cavaliero, John Cleese, James Cosmo, Peter Egan, Shobna Gulati, Anne Reid. Sitcom. Phil is worried that Edith's old flame Bob may be gaining ground and that his own one-time floozy Desiree may put in an unwelcome appearance.

1601406000.title: Unforgotten
1601406000.descr: A cop show which gets a lot of things right. The leads are convincing and realistic, the plots are complex but not too complicated, the procedural elements are spot on and the basic humanity of the victims, their families and the other characters is compelling. Nicola Walker plays DCI Cassie Stuart and she is partnered with DS Sunil "Sunny" Khan (Sanjeev Bhaskar) as they are tasked with investigating crimes from the past.

1601408700.title: Happy Valley
1601408700.descr: John feels the pressure both at work and at home, prompting him to take drastic action, while Catherine focuses on a human trafficking case, but Tommy's mum's funeral brings her face-to-face with him once again.

1601412000.title: W1A
1601412000.descr: Following on from the BAFTA award-winning Twenty Twelve: the BBC has a new Head of Values, Ian Fletcher and he's been given the huge task of sorting the corporation out, he has to "restructure" it. The BBC is becoming under a huge load of pressure with the content that they produce. This British comedy is the BBC realising where it goes wrong and is essentially criticising itself.

1601413800.title: Our Girl
1601413800.descr: Set in the time of Britain's withdrawal from Afghanistan, Our Girl follows the journeys of female medics. It all began when teenage girl Molly found herself in the army's recruitment office, after being sick in the doorway having celebrated her eighteenth birthday. Since then, there has been incredible displays of love, laughs, and loss.
